    Scope and Contents
Keith, central Illinois farmer, discusses early 20th century farm life and agriculture: farm childhood, foods, farming methods, implements, livestock, Christmas celebrations, starting his own farm, Depression, and funeral practices. Also mentions home remedies and women and children on the farm. 1 tape, 90 mins., 30 pp.
Interview by Mary Ann Dillon, 1974 
